    <abstract abstract-type="toc">
      <p>As part of a cluster of articles leading up to the 2012 World Health Report and critically
        reflecting on the theme of “no health without research,” Suerie Moon and colleagues argue
        for a global health R&amp;D treaty to improve innovation in new medicines and strengthening
        affordability, sustainable financing, efficiency in innovation, and equitable
        health-centered governance.</p>
